 oh yea, the beer...<br>
After playing for the ammount of time ive had to experience the game, literally, ive learned many things that make me just wanna slap up some VI employees and tell them the way it should be, ya know, of course ya do. (if you work for VI and you are reading this, consider yourself slapped upside the head, kthkx) One of my biggest rants is the fact that yes bla bla bla the warrior class has yet to be upgraded bla bla bla, you can bitch and moan all you want, but it doesnt make sense to me really, when you just sit back and realize you just tanked ubermobconsred_04 of your guild raid, and that 60 sk and that 60 pally tried already, and failed, miserably. i laugh everytime i see a non-warrior MA or MT, or whatever you wanna call tanking the mob for your raiding party. but its not only that, most of the time i see fellow warriors who put our names to shame, i recently moved servers, and found myself in situations with luclin mobs and what not, where i tanked better in full crafted than a 60 warrior with full ss, you wonder in awe obviously, but yes, there should be some sort of intelligence meeter on this game or sompin. no, wait...mah spelling sucks nm. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but anyway, i think what we really need to do is focus on what we are doing, to quite ranting and raving about such and such nerf/upgrade to such and such class. think about it like this, we are the guide rule for all other classes, notice ALL other classes. the reason we have not changed, at all, is this fact. they change us or upgrade us, then everything else is thrown out of wack from what VIprogrammer_06 is trying to do. you kinda see where im going? too much trouble has already been done, and to fix a bad fix is not really fixing. yea, anyway.../beer<br>
